{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{Use British English|date=June 2016}} {{infobox football biography | name = James Adlington | image = | fullname = | height = | position = [[Outside right]] | birth_date = May 1872 | birth_place = [[Shifnal]], England | death_date = | death_place = | years1 = 1892–1895 | clubs1 = [[Ironbridge F.C.|Ironbridge]] | years2 = 1895–1896 | clubs2 = [[Birmingham City F.C.|Small Heath]] | caps2 = 6 | goals2 = 4 | years3 = 1896–1897 | clubs3 = [[Worcester City F.C.|Berwick Rangers (Worcester)]] | caps3 = | goals3 = | years4 = 1897–???? | clubs4 = [[Stourport Swifts F.C.|Stourport Swifts]] }} '''James H. Adlington''' (1872 – after 1896) was an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who played in [[the Football League]] for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Small Heath]].<ref name=Joyce>{{cite book |last=Joyce |first=Michael |title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939 |publisher=SoccerData (Tony Brown) |location=Nottingham |year=2004 |page=8 |isbn=978-1-899468-67-6}}</ref> He played as an [[outside right]].
Adlington was born in [[Shifnal]], [[Shropshire]]. He began his football career with [[Ironbridge F.C.|Ironbridge]], and joined [[Birmingham City F.C.|Small Heath]] in August 1895.<ref name=Matthews68>{{cite book |last=Matthews |first=Tony |title=Birmingham City: A Complete Record |year=1995 |publisher=Breedon Books |location=Derby |page=68 |isbn=978-1-85983-010-9}}</ref> He made his debut in the [[Football League First Division|First Division]] on 23 November 1895, deputising for [[Jack Hallam (footballer)|Jack Hallam]] in a home game against [[Preston North End]] which Small Heath won 5–2.<ref>Matthews, p. 143.</ref> Adlington, a pacy player, scored in four of his next five games, but lost his place and never played for the club again. He returned to [[non-league football]] with [[Worcester City F.C.|Berwick Rangers (Worcester)]] and then [[Stourport Swifts F.C.|Stourport Swifts]].<ref name=Matthews68/>
